      • getPacketSize

        public java.lang.Integer getPacketSize()
        Returns the value of field 'packetSize'. The field 'packetSize' has the following description: Specifies the size of media packets in milliseconds. Defaults to 20 milliseconds. Possible values are 10-60 in multiples of 10. Recommended to use default. If you don't use default, you must also administer Communication Manager to change the codec of the network region where the phone belongs. Optional.
        Returns:
        Integer

      • getRtcpAddress

        public IPAddress getRtcpAddress()
        Returns the value of field 'rtcpAddress'. The field 'rtcpAddress' has the following description: Specifies IPAddress for Real Time Control Protocol. This includes the IP address and port number. Conditional. If no RTP address was specified, then do not specify an RTCP address. If an RTP address was specified, then specify the odd UDP port address that immediately follows the RTP address.
        Returns:
        IPAddress

      • getRtpAddress

        public IPAddress getRtpAddress()
        Returns the value of field 'rtpAddress'. The field 'rtpAddress' has the following description: Specifies IPAddress for RTP. This includes the IP address and port number. Specifies the Real Time Protocol address where the media should be directed. Defaults to connector server address so that connector server handles the media. If application wishes to handle the media, then specify an even UDP port address. Optional.
        Returns:
        IPAddress
